Media personality Maureen Esisi has chided a man who, in an attempt to woo her, stylishly dropped his number on a piece of paper. The socialite referred to this gesture as foolish. She said the owner of the number had failed the test and would have passed if he wrote the number on a dollar note.   My father has spent 3 weeks with abductors – Uche…     Jide Kene speaks on caucus in Nollywood     Anticipate my new single Pemi Samba, says Lobor   According to her: “So someone sent me a number today while sitting down. “My question is why are you guys so h@rny? “Why can’t you write this number on a $100 dollar bill or a 50 pound bill? “I would have called you straight away. No respect. I can’t call this number. You failed the test.”